overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  agent began by conducting a thorough code review to understand the existing
  styling and identified several areas for improvement, including the color
  palette, layout, form elements, and overall visual interest. A new
  sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and various UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and the progress bar were enhanced. The
  main questionnaire form and the introductory section were redesigned with
  subtle background elements, improved visual hierarchy, and interactive
  features. All questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent visual
  grouping and styling. During the process, a console error related to
  values in input fields was identified and resolved. After a review, the user
  pointed out remaining color inconsistencies in the Report section, which had
  hardcoded gradients. The agent then updated these hardcoded colors to align
  with the new sleep-themed palette, ensuring a cohesive and polished aesthetic
  throughout the entire application.
